Suppose $173\cdot 927\equiv n\pmod{50}$, where $0\le n< 50$.

What is the value of $n$?

$173 \cdot 927 \equiv n \pmod{50}$

$173 \equiv 23 \pmod{50}$
$927 \equiv 27 \pmod{50}$

$173 \cdot 927 \equiv 23 \cdot 27 \pmod{50}$

$23 \cdot 27 = 621$
$621 = 12 \cdot 50 + 21$

$621 \equiv 21 \pmod{50}$

Final Answer: $\boxed{21}$
